[[Category:OntologySync-managed-resource]]

The UCLA Miniscope Project is an open-source initiative to democratize in vivo calcium imaging by providing designs, software, and documentation for building miniature head-mounted fluorescence microscopes. These Miniscopes allow researchers to record the activity of hundreds to thousands of neurons in freely behaving animals.

== Miniscope Versions ==
* '''V3''' — single-wavelength excitation, ~3.3 g, first widely adopted version
* '''V4''' — redesigned optics with electronic focus, ~2.6 g, improved field of view

[[File:Miniscope-v4.png]]

== Key Features ==
* Open-source hardware and software
* Compatible with GRIN lens implants for deep brain imaging
* Works with GCaMP and other fluorescent indicators
* Data acquisition via lightweight coaxial cable (wired) or wireless link

